    <para id="id10413281"><emphasis effect="bold">AE_Tutorial 13_Problems on TUNED AMPLIFIER</emphasis>
    </para>
    <para id="id14773516">Problems have been taken from “Microelectronic Circuit Design” by R.C.Jaeger &amp; T.N.Blalock, McGraw Hill Publibcation,2006.</para>
    <para id="id11064322">Problem(1)</para>
    <para id="id11064326">Design a tuned amplifier having f<sub>o</sub>=1MHz, 3dB BW=10kHz and resonance gain= -g<sub>m</sub>R<sub>C</sub>= -10, Use a FET which at the given bias point g<sub>m</sub>=5mA/V and r<sub>o</sub>=10kΩ.</para>
